Class ExternType.Top

java.lang.Object

ExternType
Enclosing interface:
ExternType
public static final class ExternType.Top extends Object implements ExternType
The top type. This is the identity of intersection(ExternType).

Every func, global, memory and table is an instance of this type, but nothing has this as its only type. The only purpose of this is to serve as the identity of intersection.

    • intersection

      public ExternType intersection(ExternType other)
      Description copied from interface: ExternType
      Returns the most general type which is the subtype of both this and the other, or null (representing the bottom type) if no such actual type exists.

      The result of this is guaranteed to be such that this and other are both ExternType.assignableFrom(ExternType) the result.

      Formally, this is the greatest lower bound (infimum) of the subtyping relation.
